{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"499b","heading":"Participation in United States Strategic Command strategic deterrence exercises","label":"499b Participation in United States Strategic Command strategic deterrence exercises","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/stA/ptI/ch24","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Participation","label":"a .—Participation","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs is encouraged to participate in each such exercise that occurs during an even-numbered year;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Deputy Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs is encouraged to participate in each such exercise that occurs during an odd-numbered year;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Under Secretary of Defense for Policy shall participate, in whole or in part, in each such exercise;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fa%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Vice Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff shall participate, in whole or in part, in each such exercise;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fa%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"appropriate senior staff of the Executive Office of the President or appropriate organizations supporting the White House relating to continuity of government activities are encouraged to participate in each such exercise;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fa%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"appropriate general or flag officers of the military departments, and appropriate employees of Federal agencies in Senior Executive Service positions (as defined in ), shall participate, in whole or in part, in each such exercise, to provide relevant expertise to the Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs and the Deputy Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs; andsection 3132 of title 5","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":null,"label":"7","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fa%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a/7/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fa%2F7%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Commander.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a/7/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fa%2F7%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Deputy Commander.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a/7/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fa%2F7%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Director of the Joint Staff for Operations.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a/7/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/a/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fa%2F7%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Director of the Joint Staff for Strategic Plans and Policy.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Briefing","label":"b .—Briefing","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not fewer than once every four years (or more frequently if appropriate) during the period specified in subsection (a), the President shall be provided a briefing on the annual strategic deterrence exercise held by the United States Strategic Command during the year in which the briefing is provided, including the principal findings resulting from the exercise.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Reports","label":"c .—Reports","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/c/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fc%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A description of the purpose and scope of the exercise.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/c/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fc%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"An identification of the principal personnel participating in the exercise.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/c/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fc%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A statement of the principal findings resulting from the exercise that specifically relate to the nuclear command, control, and communications or senior leader decision-making process and a description of any deficiencies in that process identified a result of the exercise.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/c/1/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fc%2F1%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Whether the President was briefed on the exercise and the principal findings resulting from the exercise.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an unedited copy of the report of the Commander submitted under paragraph (1); and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/c/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499b/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499b%2Fc%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any additional recommendations or other matters the Secretary considers appropriate.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]}
